# Environment variables

## Frontend (Vercel / local `.env`)

```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
```

Get these from **Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API**.

Only the **anon** key belongs in the frontend. Never put the service role key in Vite env vars.

---

## Supabase Edge Function secrets

Set in **Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets** (or via CLI):

```env
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxx
RFQ_NOTIFICATION_TO=info@kcdesignmfg.com
RFQ_NOTIFICATION_FROM=K&C RFQ <rfq@your-verified-domain.com>
```

- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — server-side only; used to read RFQ records and file metadata
- `RESEND_API_KEY` — from [resend.com](https://resend.com); used to email K&C when an RFQ is submitted
- `RFQ_NOTIFICATION_FROM` — must be a verified sender/domain in Resend

---

## Setup checklist

1. Create a Supabase project
2. Run migrations:
   - `supabase/migrations/001_create_rfq_requests.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/002_admin_rfq_policies.sql`
3. Create an admin user in Supabase Auth (Dashboard → Authentication → Users)
4. Deploy edge function: `supabase functions deploy send-rfq-notification`
5. Add Edge Function secrets listed above
6. Add frontend env vars to Vercel (or local `.env`)
7. Deploy the Vite site
8. Sign in at `/admin/rfqs` with your Supabase admin user

---

## RFQ workflow

1. Visitor submits form → insert `rfq_requests`
2. Files upload to private bucket `rfq-files` at `rfq/{id}/{timestamp}-{filename}`
3. File metadata saved to `rfq_files`
4. Edge Function `send-rfq-notification` emails `info@kcdesignmfg.com` via Resend
